.TH "sfwbar-network" "1" "" ""
.SH Name
sfwbar-network \- Sfwbar Network module
.sp
Filename: network.so
.sp
Requires: none
.SH SYNOPSIS
.sp
The network module tracks the state of the current network connection.
.SH Triggers
.sp
The module defines trigger \fInetwork\fP which is emitted whenever the interface
properties change (i.e. ip, netmask, default gateway or wifi essid).
.SH Functions
.SS NetInfo(Query [,Interface])
.sp
Function NetInfo queries a property of the the network interface specified.
If \fIInterface\fP is not specified, NetInfo will query the interface of the
default gateway (if one exists). The queries supported are:
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \fIip\fP
IP address of the interface.
.TP
.B \fImask\fP
Net mask of the interface.
.TP
.B \fIcidr\fP
Net mask in the CIDR notation.
.TP
.B \fIgateway\fP
The default gateway (not necessarily associated with the interface).
.TP
.B \fIip6\fP
IPv6 IP address of the interface.
.TP
.B \fImask6\fP
IPv6 netmask of the interface.
.TP
.B \fIgateway6\fP
The default IPv6 gateway.
.TP
.B \fIessid\fP
ESSID of the wireless connection (if applicable for the interface).
.UNINDENT
.sp
NetInfo returns a string value.
.SS NetStat(Query [,Interface])
.sp
Function NetStat queries statistics of the interface. If the interface isn\(aqt
specified, it will be applied to the interface of the default gateway.
The queries supported are:
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \fIrxrate\fP
Receive data rate on the interface (in bps).
.TP
.B \fItxrate\fP
Transmit data rate on the interface (in bps).
.TP
.B \fIsignal\fP
Signal strength of the wifi connection (if applicable).
.UNINDENT
.sp
NetState returns a numeric value.
